track_notes: I missed the trail off Taylors Chapel Road, so it is bit shorter than it shows here.

7.2 mile loop hike with 2400 of EG and 2400 of EL from the Black Rock Mtn State Park hikers parking lot.  The hike to the summit both descends ~1200 and then regains it over 3.6 miles - pattern repeats itself on the rest of the loop out.  Accessing the summit from the southern ridge seems like a better choice - open forest but steep.  The northern part of the loop has some nice creeks and waterfalls.  You could park down at Black Rock Mtn Lake and eliminate half of the up and half of the down.
track_title: W4G/NG-045 - Marsen Knob via Edmonds Loop Trail

track_notes: NZ4R and I parked on Taylors Chapel Road where it crosses the Edmonds Trail. Head East on the trail. At Scrugg Gap, you will intersect a road. From here, begin your bushwhack ascent of the South ridge. The summit has a lot of deadfall and dense vegetation, but aim for (34.92684, -83.39776) and you will find a rock face clear and flat enough for a great activation point. It is a bit South of the true summit but well within the AZ.
